WEBVTT

00:02.212 --> 00:04.005
<i>Last season on Sneaky Pete...</i>

00:04.047 --> 00:05.632
There was a... a tyre swing.

00:05.673 --> 00:07.383
That's what I remember the most.

00:07.425 --> 00:09.344
Every summer, Grandpa would fix it.

00:09.385 --> 00:11.804
Pete, would you shut the hell up?

00:12.805 --> 00:17.143
Three years in here, I feel like I've spent
every moment of that listening to this crap.

00:19.646 --> 00:20.772
You're a con man.

00:21.189 --> 00:23.650
You, what? You tried to rob
a gun range at gunpoint?

00:23.691 --> 00:26.778
I get outta here in two days, you're not
even up for parole for another two years.

00:31.366 --> 00:32.784
Hi, Grandma, Grandpa.

00:32.825 --> 00:33.785
It's me, Pete.

00:33.826 --> 00:36.287
I called the whole family over,
all your cousins.

00:36.996 --> 00:37.914
<i>Great.</i>

00:38.790 --> 00:41.084
- Taylor, I love you.
- You should be with me.

00:41.751 --> 00:44.963
I should have said it on the day
he proposed, but I am saying it now.

00:45.004 --> 00:46.589
I want my money, Otto.

00:47.465 --> 00:48.508
Oh, motherfucker...

00:50.760 --> 00:52.095
I'm here to talk about this one.

00:52.136 --> 00:55.765
He's no use to you, but he's still the
father of my son, so, I need him alive.

00:55.807 --> 00:56.683
So, talk.

01:00.228 --> 01:01.271
What're you doing?

01:01.396 --> 01:04.566
Maybe there's still time
to un-ring that bell.

01:06.025 --> 01:08.861
I don't need the money.
I need someone to launder it.

01:09.654 --> 01:11.322
<i>I need you to tail somebody.</i>

01:11.489 --> 01:14.117
If we do this, you teach us some shit.

01:14.200 --> 01:15.910
You wanna learn something?
OK, fine, first lesson:

01:15.952 --> 01:17.912
lose the boyfriend, then we'll talk.

01:19.038 --> 01:21.791
- So, what's going on?
- I need to find someone who paints houses.

01:22.375 --> 01:23.668
And all I need to know...

01:24.586 --> 01:25.670
is who you want gone.

01:26.921 --> 01:27.922
You're looking at him.

01:29.549 --> 01:31.718
Everybody get on the fucking ground!

01:42.645 --> 01:47.025
There's a cop here looking for Pete,
a New York cop named Winslow.

01:47.108 --> 01:49.694
Listen to me, Carly, I want you to
tell them that you do not consent

01:49.736 --> 01:51.112
to a search of your residence.

01:54.073 --> 01:54.949
Audrey!

01:56.117 --> 01:57.076
I'm in trouble.

01:57.118 --> 01:58.369
Grandma!

01:58.953 --> 02:01.164
You can't be a part of this!

02:01.205 --> 02:02.081
I already am.

02:09.172 --> 02:10.048
Hey, Pete.

02:10.173 --> 02:11.382
Do I know you guys?

02:11.424 --> 02:12.300
No.

02:13.217 --> 02:14.135
Gina.

02:14.385 --> 02:16.095
I want you to take us to your mother

02:17.639 --> 02:19.182
and the $11 million.

02:24.270 --> 02:26.230
- Where's your mother, Pete?
- I don't know.

02:27.398 --> 02:28.316
You don't know?

02:29.067 --> 02:31.444
The fuck kinda stupid answer
is "you don't know"?

02:31.486 --> 02:33.780
What's to keep us
from snapping your string right now?

02:34.739 --> 02:37.992
Because I know how to find her
and you don't.

02:39.327 --> 02:40.828
Huh. Let's go, then.

02:43.247 --> 02:49.170
<i>♪ Set the sails
I feel the winds a'stirring ♪</i>

02:53.424 --> 02:55.593
<i>- ♪ Towards the bright... ♪</i>
- How did you, uh...?

02:57.303 --> 02:58.554
"How did we, uh," what?

02:59.013 --> 03:01.974
How... how'd you figure it out?

03:03.643 --> 03:04.560
My mother and me?

03:06.854 --> 03:10.525
None of the guys our employer hired
before us bothered to ask

03:10.566 --> 03:13.861
what else happened at Mount Vernon
the day the 11 million was stolen.

03:14.028 --> 03:16.823
They never figured out some fucking idiot
robbed a gun range.

03:17.323 --> 03:18.533
Although I do get that a lot.

03:18.574 --> 03:20.952
People asking what kind of fucking idiot
robs a gun range.

03:20.993 --> 03:21.869
Every day.

03:22.829 --> 03:26.666
Now, where we got smart was wondering,
what if you're not an idiot?

03:27.417 --> 03:29.669
First dot we connected
was the security guard.

03:30.002 --> 03:33.089
We could put him at the gun range
right before you made your entrance.

03:33.131 --> 03:35.216
Ten minutes later, he's back at work

03:35.842 --> 03:36.968
dying in the shootout.

03:37.009 --> 03:39.929
You were trying to hold him there, huh?
Keep him from getting back?

03:40.304 --> 03:43.433
It's too bad it didn't work.
I mean, you went to jail for fucking nothing.

03:43.474 --> 03:45.309
How, how'd you know that I was out?

03:45.685 --> 03:48.020
Oh, we got a guy, built a bot

03:48.646 --> 03:50.481
looks for anything to do with you
or your mother.

03:51.774 --> 03:54.652
Last week it sees your name pop up
on an airline ticket.

03:56.654 --> 03:59.323
<i>OK, two tickets for the 5:20
to Fort Lauderdale.</i>

03:59.532 --> 04:01.492
<i>You wanna go to Buffalo
or Fort Lauderdale?</i>

04:01.534 --> 04:04.120
<i>Do we only get to go
if we have good reasons for wanting to go?</i>

04:04.245 --> 04:06.748
- You didn't board the flight.
- No, I had to buy a ticket

04:06.789 --> 04:09.167
to get through security.
We were tracing a skip.

04:10.001 --> 04:11.294
My, uh, my cousin and me.

04:11.794 --> 04:12.712
Pretty blonde?

04:32.398 --> 04:33.274
Where you going now?

04:35.568 --> 04:37.820
I'm, uh, going to New York.

04:37.862 --> 04:40.281
Terms of my parole.
I'm not supposed to be in Connecticut.

04:40.740 --> 04:42.158
Just had to see the family, huh?

04:43.242 --> 04:47.413
We'll be watching them. You try warning them,
or we see them go into hiding...

04:47.455 --> 04:48.539
But you won't do that.

04:49.040 --> 04:51.209
Cos you're gonna be too busy
trying to find your mum.

04:51.876 --> 04:54.629
You got 72 hours
before we start clipping their wires.

04:55.254 --> 04:56.881
That pretty blonde girl goes first.

05:07.308 --> 05:09.644
- You should run.
<i>- It's 11 million dollars.</i>

05:10.102 --> 05:12.188
And what happens when the FBI
picks you up

05:12.230 --> 05:13.815
for what played out in Vince's poker room?

05:13.856 --> 05:16.150
- They're not even looking for me.
<i>- Their agent was shot.</i>

05:16.192 --> 05:17.568
Money is missing. They're looking for you.

05:17.610 --> 05:21.155
Wha... but they can't prove anything.
Marjorie, come on.

05:21.197 --> 05:22.281
<i>That's not what I mean.</i>

05:22.323 --> 05:25.117
If these two goons see you
getting scooped up by the FBI

05:25.159 --> 05:28.621
and they find out that you're not Pete,
what's to stop them from killing you?

05:28.955 --> 05:30.373
<i>Well, I'll think of something.</i>

05:30.414 --> 05:33.292
Marjorie, we're talking about
11 million dollars.

05:33.543 --> 05:35.378
Alright.

05:36.254 --> 05:37.755
How do you propose on finding it?

05:38.589 --> 05:40.842
- You don't have much to go on.
<i>- I know that</i>

05:40.883 --> 05:44.512
ten minutes after Pete robbed a gun range,
there was a big shootout

05:44.554 --> 05:46.305
that left a security guard dead.

05:46.430 --> 05:48.224
There's gotta be
something online about that

05:48.266 --> 05:50.351
and then I got their license plate number.

05:50.893 --> 05:53.771
Y'know, I just don't have a computer, so--

05:53.813 --> 05:55.147
Marius, I'm retired.

05:55.189 --> 05:57.066
I just need you to do a little bit
of research.

05:57.108 --> 05:59.193
- Then I will expect a lot of money.
<i>- OK, OK.</i>

05:59.235 --> 06:01.654
- I'll give you 5% of whatever I get.
<i>- Mm.</i>

06:01.696 --> 06:03.447
I wish I didn't answer this phone.

06:04.031 --> 06:04.907
Alright.

06:05.992 --> 06:08.452
I assume there was a threat to go along
with all of this?

06:08.494 --> 06:11.414
Yeah, they said they were gonna kill
the whole family starting with Julia.

06:11.455 --> 06:12.331
<i>Oh, that's great.</i>

06:14.542 --> 06:15.751
Bernhardt Bail Bonds.

06:16.002 --> 06:16.878
<i>Audrey?</i>

06:16.961 --> 06:18.880
Uh, no, this is Julia. May I help you?

06:18.921 --> 06:19.839
<i>Little Blondie?</i>

06:20.715 --> 06:21.632
- Uh...
<i>- Shit.</i>

06:22.008 --> 06:24.385
<i>You don't remember me? This is Luis.
Luis Mercado.</i>

06:24.427 --> 06:25.553
Of course I remember you.

06:25.761 --> 06:28.097
<i>Little Blondie,
answering the phones and shit.</i>

06:28.472 --> 06:29.557
<i>Hey, is Otto around?</i>

06:29.599 --> 06:30.474
Not right now.

06:30.850 --> 06:32.268
<i>OK. Well, have him hit me back.</i>

06:32.810 --> 06:35.104
- Can I ask what this is about?
<i>- Just have him call.</i>

06:35.146 --> 06:37.648
<i>Hey, I bet you don't still wear your hair
in pigtails?</i>

06:37.690 --> 06:39.609
Heh. Not so much.

06:40.067 --> 06:40.943
<i>Ha!</i>

06:50.912 --> 06:53.456
I'm starting to think
you're just making excuses to see me.

06:54.999 --> 06:58.628
I was running the numbers and I
thought you should hear this in person.

06:58.669 --> 07:00.504
Sounds like I'm gonna be disappointed.

07:00.755 --> 07:02.924
In order to launder your 150

07:02.965 --> 07:06.010
I'm gonna have to write fake bonds
for fake people

07:06.052 --> 07:09.513
and then put their fake deposits,
your cash, in the bank.

07:09.555 --> 07:12.516
That should take three to four months.

07:14.185 --> 07:18.147
If you need it faster,
you could take it to Mohegan

07:18.606 --> 07:20.441
turn it into poker chips.

07:20.691 --> 07:21.567
Let me guess.

07:22.318 --> 07:23.945
You Googled how to launder money

07:23.986 --> 07:26.155
and the plot of that movie
with Captain Kirk came up.

07:27.573 --> 07:28.449
You see it?

07:28.991 --> 07:29.867
It's good.

07:31.118 --> 07:35.539
Anyway, what they don't say in the film
is that the casinos now have RFID

07:35.581 --> 07:37.625
in the chips to show
that they've been gambled.

07:39.794 --> 07:41.420
You want to give the money back, huh?

07:42.630 --> 07:44.465
Don't forget why you're in this situation.

07:45.091 --> 07:48.636
You offered a service to get the father
of your son out of an early grave.

07:48.886 --> 07:53.057
You withdraw that service, what's to keep
something from happening to him?

07:53.099 --> 07:56.102
Or, God forbid,
someone you actually care about.

07:56.978 --> 07:58.396
Three months is too long.

07:58.854 --> 08:00.523
I need the money back by next week.

08:36.475 --> 08:40.688
You got me where I needed to go, but...
your heart didn't seem in it.

08:42.565 --> 08:43.441
Ah, shit.

08:45.192 --> 08:47.153
I hope you don't give me
a bad review on Yelp.

08:49.905 --> 08:51.615
You wanted to talk about something?

08:53.325 --> 08:55.995
Why d'you think Sean's
been going to Hartford so much?

08:58.080 --> 09:00.499
I haven't cared about Hartford
since the Whalers left.

09:02.960 --> 09:07.798
He's been lobbying to have Connecticut
do bail bonds like Kentucky.

09:09.050 --> 09:10.092
Where the state runs it.

09:10.509 --> 09:12.094
That would put him out of business.

09:13.012 --> 09:16.849
Not if he gets the contract to run it.

09:19.977 --> 09:22.188
That'd put Grandpa and Grandma
out of business.

09:24.231 --> 09:25.107
But you...

09:26.442 --> 09:29.987
would have a shit-ton of money
to help them in their retirement.

09:30.738 --> 09:34.825
I wait for Sean's deal to go through,
and then I divorce him

09:34.867 --> 09:39.663
get half of everything, and you and I
get married on a beach in Hawaii.

09:46.170 --> 09:47.421
You don't seem thrilled.

09:51.926 --> 09:52.802
Look, I...

09:54.470 --> 09:56.722
I like money as much as the next guy

09:58.641 --> 10:00.309
but I want to be with you now.

10:01.685 --> 10:02.895
Just gotta be patient.

10:07.274 --> 10:10.486
<i>We continue this romantic journey
with Brad in Costa Ric--</i>

10:14.532 --> 10:15.783
Thing One and Thing Two?

10:16.450 --> 10:17.326
Asleep.

10:20.121 --> 10:21.080
I like your new purse.

10:22.081 --> 10:23.624
Oh! Found it in the car.

10:23.791 --> 10:27.128
Ellen won't use it anymore,
says pink is for babies.

10:27.169 --> 10:29.672
Has to be the purple
or she throws a shit-fit.

10:34.927 --> 10:35.845
Hey, um...

10:36.887 --> 10:39.765
can you stay the night,
take care of the squids in the morning?

10:40.015 --> 10:43.102
Mr Ambien is dangling a good night's sleep.

10:44.436 --> 10:47.148
Sure. But I'm keeping track
of what you owe me.

10:47.648 --> 10:48.607
Of course you are.

10:54.405 --> 10:56.907
Hey, did Pete say
where he was going when he left?

10:57.408 --> 10:58.450
No. Why?

10:59.451 --> 11:00.870
I need to talk to him about something.

11:01.954 --> 11:02.830
Night.

11:21.640 --> 11:22.516
Hey.

11:22.558 --> 11:24.727
<i>Car belongs to a leasing company in Queens.</i>

11:24.768 --> 11:27.396
To get who leased it would require
tools and skills I do not have.

11:27.438 --> 11:28.314
<i>What about...</i>

11:28.355 --> 11:30.691
- What about tomorrow?
<i>- The last I find any mention</i>

11:30.733 --> 11:33.110
<i>of Maggie Murphy is three years ago
in New Orleans.</i>

11:33.777 --> 11:35.946
And the, uh... the shootout?

11:35.988 --> 11:37.531
<i>Ten minutes after Pete</i>

11:37.573 --> 11:38.657
<i>walked into a gun range</i>

11:38.699 --> 11:41.869
there was a shootout at a nearby
storage facility that left three dead.

11:41.911 --> 11:43.621
<i>- Two guards and--</i>
- And a security guard.

11:43.662 --> 11:46.707
Yes, and before he shuffled off
this mortal coil

11:47.082 --> 11:50.211
the guard said two people got away,
one of whom was

11:50.252 --> 11:51.754
<i>a white woman in her fifties.</i>

11:52.004 --> 11:55.257
<i>And having recently played Pete's mum,
I know that description fits.</i>

11:55.716 --> 11:59.970
So 11 million dollars was stolen
from a storage facility?

12:00.012 --> 12:01.847
<i>No. At least, not officially.</i>

12:01.889 --> 12:02.932
<i>In none of the reports</i>

12:02.973 --> 12:06.018
is there any mention of 11 million,
or anything else being stolen.

12:06.060 --> 12:07.269
<i>What does that tell you?</i>

12:07.645 --> 12:09.688
Well, it was stolen from a criminal.

12:09.730 --> 12:12.483
<i>That's right, and any criminal
with 11 million dollars</i>

12:12.524 --> 12:13.943
isn't just any criminal.

12:14.568 --> 12:16.779
It could be some hedge fund guy, I mean...

12:16.946 --> 12:18.822
<i>With goons who threaten to kill a family?</i>

12:18.906 --> 12:21.992
<i>Marius, before you go looking
for Pete's mum or the money</i>

12:22.117 --> 12:24.245
I'd say your first order of business
is to find out

12:24.286 --> 12:25.579
who the fuck you're dealing with.

12:32.044 --> 12:34.463
♪ It's getting harder out here ♪

12:36.840 --> 12:39.927
♪ I keep tryin' to just make my way ♪

12:40.970 --> 12:42.429
♪ It's not lyin' ♪

12:45.182 --> 12:46.642
♪ I'm only tryin' ♪

12:50.396 --> 12:52.314
♪ Just trust in me ♪

12:52.773 --> 12:54.483
♪ Trust in me ♪

12:54.733 --> 12:56.777
♪ Just trust in me ♪

12:57.319 --> 12:58.862
♪ Trust in me ♪

12:59.238 --> 13:01.198
♪ Just trust in me. ♪

13:17.631 --> 13:19.800
♪ Let it be and let it be free ♪

13:23.429 --> 13:25.389
♪ Let it be and let it be free... ♪

13:43.365 --> 13:45.159
You're quite the creature of habit.

13:47.911 --> 13:48.871
Fuck me.

13:48.954 --> 13:51.749
You gotta think about changing up
your hunting grounds, buddy.

13:51.790 --> 13:54.793
Yeah, I don't need any of your lessons,
asshole. What do you want?

13:54.918 --> 13:55.794
Open the door.

13:56.003 --> 13:57.254
I'm looking for Gina.

13:57.546 --> 13:59.131
You and Gina can go fuck yourselves.

13:59.173 --> 14:01.091
Hey, in ten seconds
I'm gonna call for the police

14:01.133 --> 14:03.093
and then I'm gonna tell 'em
I found the guy who took my wallet.

14:03.344 --> 14:04.803
I don't have your wallet.

14:14.938 --> 14:17.232
That's your wallet, asshole.

14:20.736 --> 14:21.612
Where is she?

14:22.154 --> 14:24.990
Grandma, I strongly suggest
that you don't do this.

14:26.158 --> 14:28.744
- Father Lebec is a man of God.
- He is a man.

14:29.411 --> 14:31.288
He, he could let it slip.

14:32.247 --> 14:33.749
I'll only tell him what he can hear.

14:33.791 --> 14:35.209
- I won't--
- Please, please, Grandma.

14:35.250 --> 14:37.753
Please, I'm... I'm begging you, OK?

14:38.796 --> 14:42.341
Not now. Just give it a week.
Let this blow over.

14:42.716 --> 14:45.302
It's gonna blow over in a week?
A cop was killed.

14:46.345 --> 14:49.598
Yeah, well, Fairfield's got the case.
They're not idiots but...

14:50.015 --> 14:51.183
they're idiot-adjacent.

14:53.685 --> 14:54.561
Grandma?

14:56.688 --> 14:57.940
Tell me you will hold off.

14:57.981 --> 14:58.857
OK.

15:00.776 --> 15:01.652
OK.

15:02.820 --> 15:04.113
I gotta go, alright?

15:04.613 --> 15:06.115
Where's Carly? She need a ride?

15:06.740 --> 15:08.117
She stayed at Julia's.

15:08.826 --> 15:09.701
OK.

15:13.497 --> 15:15.082
- Grandma?
- Yeah.

15:24.883 --> 15:26.343
You gonna do what he said?

15:27.928 --> 15:29.638
That's what confession was made for.

15:30.347 --> 15:32.558
So we can be absolved of our sins.

15:34.143 --> 15:38.439
You didn't do anything that needs absolving.
It was an accident.

15:38.856 --> 15:42.484
There's a long list of bad decisions
that put me in a car with a gun.

15:44.319 --> 15:45.279
I gotta run errands.

15:46.947 --> 15:48.115
I'll stop at the shop.

15:49.158 --> 15:53.203
How are you gonna handle all this?
Just drink and stare off into the distance?

15:54.746 --> 15:55.831
It worked before.

15:57.124 --> 16:00.335
Took you ten years to surface
when you came home from Vietnam.

16:03.464 --> 16:04.673
You don't have ten years.

16:24.568 --> 16:25.986
Oh, f...!

16:57.351 --> 16:58.227
You're awake.

16:58.602 --> 16:59.478
Barely.

16:59.895 --> 17:02.481
Hey, I see Ellen's backpack on the counter.

17:02.523 --> 17:03.690
<i>Yeah, so, apparently</i>

17:03.732 --> 17:07.069
someone left her lunch in there all weekend
and it smelled like a toxic waste dump

17:07.110 --> 17:08.153
so I bought her a sandwich

17:08.195 --> 17:09.279
<i>on the way to school.</i>

17:09.321 --> 17:12.324
- Did she take her old pink backpack?
<i>- Yes, she did, no fuss.</i>

17:12.491 --> 17:13.659
<i>See, I get away with stuff</i>

17:13.700 --> 17:15.827
because I am cool Aunt Carly.

17:16.370 --> 17:19.748
- Did you look inside?
<i>- We just grabbed it and ran. Why?</i>

17:19.957 --> 17:23.252
Oh, I just left some, uh, office papers

17:23.293 --> 17:25.045
<i>in there, I'll get 'em later.</i>

17:25.087 --> 17:26.630
I was wondering. It was kinda heavy.

17:26.672 --> 17:29.508
<i>Aren't there rules about how heavy
a kid's backpack should be?</i>

17:29.633 --> 17:33.303
Probably also rules about not sending kids
down the coal mines. Killjoys.

17:33.345 --> 17:36.265
<i>- Thanks for staying and wrangling.</i>
- Yeah, my pleasure.

17:36.306 --> 17:37.724
I like ta--

17:50.862 --> 17:52.364
- Where did he find you?
- The park.

17:52.656 --> 17:54.116
I told you to mix it up.

17:54.908 --> 17:56.660
We should get going before he shows.

18:00.122 --> 18:00.998
- Sorry.
- Gavin!

18:01.582 --> 18:03.333
- O... Open the door!
- It's OK, calm down.

18:03.375 --> 18:05.627
- Gavin!
- I know you set me up with those guys.

18:05.961 --> 18:07.838
What you did was part of the game.

18:11.300 --> 18:12.676
How much did they pay you?

18:15.804 --> 18:16.680
Five hundred?

18:17.973 --> 18:18.849
More?

18:19.474 --> 18:20.350
One large.

18:22.519 --> 18:26.898
Well, what if I pay you two the same to
figure out what hotel they're staying at?

18:26.940 --> 18:28.442
- How do we--
- You figure it out.

18:29.234 --> 18:30.110
Here.

18:30.485 --> 18:32.112
Here's their license plate number

18:32.154 --> 18:34.072
and I'll give you the rest
when you find them.

18:36.283 --> 18:37.159
Go ahead, take it.

18:39.036 --> 18:40.162
Adios, amigos.

18:45.792 --> 18:46.668
Asshole.

18:47.628 --> 18:48.795
- I'm the asshole?
- Yeah.

18:49.004 --> 18:49.880
You dumped me.

18:52.591 --> 18:53.467
It's good to see you.

18:54.509 --> 18:55.385
Just drive.

19:02.768 --> 19:04.061
I'm undercover security.

19:04.269 --> 19:05.604
I'm recording this conversation.

19:05.646 --> 19:07.481
I need to hear you say you agree
to come with me.

19:09.024 --> 19:10.275
I don't agree to come with you.

19:11.026 --> 19:12.110
Then I call the cops.

19:39.971 --> 19:41.515
Ellen took the wrong backpack this morning.

19:41.598 --> 19:43.058
Thanks, I'll get it to her.

19:43.100 --> 19:44.768
I better take the one she came with.

19:45.060 --> 19:46.395
You can get them both, end of day.

19:46.812 --> 19:50.232
I left her lunch leftovers in it
and if anybody accidentally opens

19:50.273 --> 19:52.609
that sucker, there is gonna be
an airborne toxic event.

19:54.277 --> 19:56.697
You know, you really should clean out
a backpack every night.

19:57.280 --> 19:59.408
- You're right.
- I'm sure you're really busy.

19:59.449 --> 20:00.325
I am.

20:00.492 --> 20:02.828
Probably why you had the au pair
drop Ellen off this morning.

20:03.286 --> 20:04.162
The au pair?

20:06.123 --> 20:07.499
That was my sister Carly.

20:07.874 --> 20:11.211
She went to this school for a year,
back when she was Ellen's age.

20:11.253 --> 20:13.922
I remember it because that was the year
our parents were killed

20:13.964 --> 20:16.299
by a drunk driver out on Redding Road.

20:20.554 --> 20:21.513
It's pink.

20:26.476 --> 20:27.936
Sorry, Mum. Sorry, Dad.

20:31.481 --> 20:32.357
Here you go.

20:43.994 --> 20:44.995
Wrong pink backpack.

20:45.662 --> 20:47.873
- Are you sure? It's the only one I saw.
- I'm sure.

20:49.750 --> 20:51.543
Oh... Wait, uh.

20:51.585 --> 20:54.755
Shelley wasn't feeling well this morning
and her mum picked her up

20:55.005 --> 20:57.257
and I think she has a pink backpack too?

20:57.299 --> 20:59.634
Shelley... Birse?

20:59.676 --> 21:01.344
No, Shelley Martin. Who's Shelley Birse?

21:01.386 --> 21:04.097
I must've heard it wrong
when Ellen said her name.

21:04.139 --> 21:06.141
Her mum is Sarah?

21:06.808 --> 21:08.643
- Gayle.
- Wow, I really got it wrong.

21:08.894 --> 21:10.437
- You want me to call--
- No, I got it, thanks.

21:11.897 --> 21:13.815
I really should be the
one to get it back...

21:14.733 --> 21:15.734
I need an address.

21:16.276 --> 21:18.695
<i>See, this is why they invented the internet</i>

21:18.737 --> 21:20.655
so that you could search
for this stuff yourself

21:20.697 --> 21:22.657
and not have your cop
brother do it for you.

21:23.116 --> 21:24.201
Gayle Martin.

21:25.285 --> 21:26.536
She better not be a skip.

21:26.578 --> 21:28.163
<i>She's the mother
of one of Ellen's classmates.</i>

21:28.205 --> 21:30.248
We're class mums for the aquarium trip.

21:30.499 --> 21:32.667
Wait, why, why can't the school office

21:32.709 --> 21:34.336
<i>- look her up for you?</i>
- Please don't make me lie anymore.

21:35.545 --> 21:37.172
I know, I know, I know...

21:39.800 --> 21:41.802
I shouldn't feel guilty,
the guy was a hitman

21:41.843 --> 21:44.805
it's the life he chose, he had to know
something could always go sideways.

21:48.850 --> 21:49.726
What?

21:50.685 --> 21:53.522
You don't feel guilty,
you feel embarrassed.

21:53.772 --> 21:56.233
You were wallowing in self-pity
and you know it.

21:56.274 --> 22:00.070
"Oh, poor me, nobody loves me,
nobody needs me

22:00.111 --> 22:01.446
I'd be better off dead."

22:01.488 --> 22:03.782
- Fuck you, kiss my ass.
- Tell me I'm wrong.

22:04.449 --> 22:06.576
I don't know what I was thinking,
asking you over.

22:07.285 --> 22:08.370
You hit on my wife.

22:08.411 --> 22:09.996
- I should punch you in the nose.
- Do it.

22:10.372 --> 22:13.166
Be better than you sitting around
feeling sorry for yourself.

22:13.208 --> 22:15.627
- Fuck you!
- You already said that.

22:20.465 --> 22:21.466
All that day

22:23.051 --> 22:23.927
I was...

22:25.595 --> 22:29.224
I just couldn't help thinking,
"This is the last time I see my wife.

22:31.351 --> 22:32.435
See this house."

22:35.355 --> 22:38.775
So nobly tragic, it was like an Irish play.

22:40.527 --> 22:42.696
"The last time I pick my nose.

22:42.737 --> 22:45.031
The last time I scratch me balls."

22:57.836 --> 22:59.546
I'd be more comfortable the old way.

23:00.630 --> 23:02.757
The new confessional will be ready
in a month.

23:04.301 --> 23:06.553
You know,
a lot of people prefer it this way

23:07.178 --> 23:09.222
just sitting and talking.

23:11.433 --> 23:12.309
Huh.

23:23.612 --> 23:25.614
Forgive me, Father, for I have sinned.

23:37.500 --> 23:39.169
- I saw you.
- Did you?

23:41.755 --> 23:43.006
Oh, shit.

23:43.590 --> 23:44.674
It was that other girl.

23:45.342 --> 23:46.509
You were just the distraction.

23:47.427 --> 23:49.095
That's also how we got JFK.

23:52.349 --> 23:53.224
Can I go now?

