♪ And the other's getting colder ♪

23:59.105 --> 24:04.527
♪ She looks so good but it's not nearly
Feeling like it's supposed to ♪

24:04.569 --> 24:07.072
♪ Going sold, going sold ♪

24:07.238 --> 24:09.366
♪ Going, gone ♪

24:11.910 --> 24:13.620
♪ Say my name again ♪

24:14.162 --> 24:16.247
♪ Tell me you're caught in the middle ♪

24:17.374 --> 24:18.917
♪ You're caught in the middle ♪

24:19.918 --> 24:22.045
♪ And you're begging for me to stay ♪

24:22.796 --> 24:24.547
♪ Cos every now and then ♪

24:25.256 --> 24:27.133
♪ My love calls like a whistle ♪

24:28.259 --> 24:29.928
♪ It calls like a whistle ♪

24:30.762 --> 24:32.973
♪ And it's blowing your mind again. ♪

24:43.650 --> 24:44.526
Marius?

24:44.901 --> 24:46.194
Hey, buddy, how's it going?

24:46.444 --> 24:49.114
I'm in prison.
How the fuck do you think it's going?

24:49.781 --> 24:52.325
Yeah, and here I thought you Buddhists
were all zen and shit.

24:53.910 --> 24:57.122
Go to Burma, see how zen and shit
those guys are.

24:57.497 --> 24:58.373
What do you want?

24:59.332 --> 25:02.919
Yeah, I need a private conversation
with my old cellie, Pete Murphy.

25:02.961 --> 25:05.755
Is your fee still $50 in your commissary?

25:06.214 --> 25:07.090
<i>Not for you.</i>

25:07.632 --> 25:09.009
- Really?
<i>- For you it's 500.</i>

25:09.551 --> 25:10.969
- Why?
- You cheated at cards.

25:11.469 --> 25:13.680
<i>- The hell I did.</i>
- The thing with the ace.

25:14.431 --> 25:16.641
That was a trick!
I bet you a pack of ramen.

25:16.850 --> 25:18.268
<i>Maybe you could show me a trick.</i>

25:18.643 --> 25:19.936
You wanna learn a card trick?

25:20.020 --> 25:21.730
<i>I got visitation on Sunday</i>

25:21.771 --> 25:24.107
and it'd be cool to show my boy something.

25:27.360 --> 25:28.486
OK. Yeah.

25:28.528 --> 25:29.571
Get a deck of cards.

26:01.853 --> 26:04.105
Well... thought you'd come by.

26:04.147 --> 26:05.565
- Did the school call?
- The school?

26:05.774 --> 26:06.649
No.

26:07.734 --> 26:10.445
These kids, you know,
they always have to have the same clothes

26:10.487 --> 26:12.238
the same backpacks, the same...

26:15.283 --> 26:17.327
Oh, this is my brother, Desmond.

26:20.038 --> 26:21.748
You didn't say what your name was.

26:25.376 --> 26:27.879
<i>OK, so now you cut the cards which means--</i>

26:27.921 --> 26:29.672
I fucking know what
cutting a deck of cards means.

26:30.090 --> 26:32.884
OK. OK, so then, just do that

26:32.926 --> 26:34.260
and start turning them over.

26:34.594 --> 26:36.638
And just keep turning them over,
you can say things like...

26:36.971 --> 26:39.599
"Is this your card? Is this your card?"
You know, when you know

26:39.641 --> 26:41.226
<i>- it isn't.</i>
- Why would I do that?

26:41.267 --> 26:43.937
<i>- Just cos it's fun to get it wrong sometimes--</i>
- I don't wanna get it wrong.

26:43.978 --> 26:45.480
I want to impress my son.

26:45.522 --> 26:47.398
OK, right, of course.

26:47.440 --> 26:51.027
So then just keep turning cards over
and when you get to whatever

26:51.069 --> 26:54.781
<i>the bottom card was before you cut the deck</i>

26:55.031 --> 26:57.575
then you'll know that the next card
is gonna be the one that he picked.

26:57.992 --> 26:58.952
Is this your card?

27:00.495 --> 27:01.371
Yeah.

27:01.621 --> 27:03.081
<i>Don't just say "Yeah."</i>

27:03.123 --> 27:04.874
<i>Act surprised, you asshole.</i>

27:05.291 --> 27:06.835
<i>Yeah, that's my card.</i>

27:07.252 --> 27:10.380
<i>- You suck.</i>
- Tenzin, your son is gonna be surprised.

27:10.630 --> 27:13.675
<i>You're damn right he'll be surprised.
This is some David Copperfield shit.</i>

27:13.716 --> 27:14.676
Yeah, just keep practising.

27:14.717 --> 27:17.053
You know, you can try it out
on people at dinner or whatever.

27:17.220 --> 27:19.013
<i>- I will, man, thanks.</i>
- Yeah, you're welcome.

27:19.055 --> 27:21.516
So you think you can get the phone
to Pete today?

27:21.558 --> 27:22.433
<i>I will.</i>

27:22.475 --> 27:24.978
As soon as you put $500 in my commissary.

27:25.478 --> 27:27.230
<i>- Five hundred? What do you mean?</i>
- That's your price.

27:28.064 --> 27:30.608
<i>The trick was just so I didn't hang up.</i>

27:34.821 --> 27:36.281
Son of a bitch.

27:44.164 --> 27:45.081
Hey. Where?

27:45.707 --> 27:48.710
<i>- Don't you wanna know how?</i>
- Honestly, I really, I...

27:48.751 --> 27:50.420
We called around,
saying we need to find our bosses

27:50.461 --> 27:52.463
job's on the line,
here's the license plate.

27:53.089 --> 27:54.465
Brilliant. So where are they?

27:54.716 --> 27:58.595
Hotel on Bank. Room 1106.
Frank and Joe Hooper.

27:58.803 --> 27:59.804
Are they there now?

28:00.430 --> 28:03.266
<i>No car in the lot.
Called the room twice, didn't get an answer.</i>

28:03.308 --> 28:07.812
Good. So get a key card,
and one of you wait in the parking lot.

28:07.854 --> 28:09.898
<i>The other, make sure the room is empty</i>

28:09.939 --> 28:11.357
and wait inside.

28:11.733 --> 28:13.401
I'll see you there in 15 minutes.

28:13.443 --> 28:14.694
How do we get a key card?

28:15.195 --> 28:16.613
Hello?

28:21.284 --> 28:22.452
Finder's fee?

28:23.411 --> 28:25.538
Thinking it's more like a shakedown fee.

28:26.039 --> 28:27.165
Call it what you want.

28:28.499 --> 28:29.375
How much?

28:34.172 --> 28:35.173
Can't do that.

28:37.091 --> 28:39.052
Des, let's just call the cops.

28:39.093 --> 28:39.969
Good idea.

28:40.136 --> 28:41.763
Look, the money's not mine.

28:43.723 --> 28:47.018
Is it OK if I at least call the person
it belongs to?

28:48.102 --> 28:49.270
Call whoever you want.

28:53.149 --> 28:54.108
Mind if I smoke?

28:54.275 --> 28:55.193
Yes, I mind.

28:55.360 --> 28:57.070
There are children living in this house.

29:05.745 --> 29:07.330
Hey. It's Julia.

29:09.374 --> 29:10.250
Where are you?

29:11.376 --> 29:12.877
Because I got a big fucking problem.

29:20.051 --> 29:21.761
- May I help you?
- I certainly hope so.

29:22.262 --> 29:23.638
I left my key in the room.

29:24.013 --> 29:25.515
- Your name, sir?
- Hooper.

29:25.556 --> 29:26.432
Frank Hooper.

29:27.141 --> 29:29.310
- And your room number?
- 1106.

29:30.353 --> 29:31.354
Very good, Mr Hooper.

29:31.396 --> 29:32.438
Do you have some ID?

29:33.106 --> 29:34.899
I do, and I left it in the room.

29:34.941 --> 29:38.152
- If you wanna come up with me I can grab--
- I don't give a fuck

29:38.194 --> 29:39.904
why they call you Kid Charlemagne!

29:40.321 --> 29:41.197
Urgh!

29:41.572 --> 29:42.615
Your "patrons"?

29:42.657 --> 29:45.660
Your patrons left you in the red, asshole!

29:45.702 --> 29:48.371
All your low-rent friends are dead.
You gotta clean that mess up

29:48.413 --> 29:50.206
or we all end up in jail.

29:50.456 --> 29:52.709
The test tubes, the scale

29:52.750 --> 29:54.585
you gotta get that shit outta there!

29:54.627 --> 29:57.338
- Ma'am?
- Don't fucking "ma'am" me.

29:58.006 --> 30:01.592
"Is there gas in the car?"
Yes, there is gas in the car!

30:06.222 --> 30:07.265
"Kid Charlemagne"?

30:07.307 --> 30:10.476
Steely Dan song. A guy that age,
no way he'd know it.

30:12.145 --> 30:14.439
- You see how well I worked him?
- Pretty slick.

30:14.772 --> 30:16.858
It's good, you and me together again.

30:16.899 --> 30:17.775
Don't push it.

30:17.817 --> 30:19.736
- I'm just saying.
- I know what you're saying.

30:26.409 --> 30:27.410
- Gayle Martin?
- Yeah.

30:27.452 --> 30:28.703
- Where is she?
- Excuse me--

30:28.745 --> 30:30.288
- Julia!
- This is my house, excuse me!

30:30.330 --> 30:32.165
- Julia, are you OK?
- Oh, yeah, I'm fine.

30:32.874 --> 30:34.334
You're better than fine

30:34.375 --> 30:36.461
You're high as a fucking kite,
I can see it in your eyes.

30:36.502 --> 30:38.087
- Lemme see your arms.
- Who are you?

30:38.838 --> 30:40.548
Who am I? Who the fuck are you?

30:40.590 --> 30:41.549
Is this your dealer?

30:41.591 --> 30:43.092
Maybe I should ask to see his arms too!

30:43.134 --> 30:45.428
The fuck are you talking about?
You can see my arms!

30:45.470 --> 30:47.722
- Tom, Tom...
- What, what part of undercover

30:47.764 --> 30:48.848
do you not understand?

30:48.973 --> 30:51.184
Huh? Is that my money on the table
right there?

30:51.225 --> 30:53.186
I had it in Ellen's old backpack
and there was a mix-up--

30:53.227 --> 30:55.313
I swear to God, if you're lying to me,
your precious little Ellen's

30:55.355 --> 30:57.231
gonna go straight
to child protective services

30:57.273 --> 30:59.442
and you're not gonna see her again
until she ages out.

30:59.484 --> 31:01.152
- No, no, please, don't...
- She's not lying!

31:01.194 --> 31:02.236
- Yeah.
- She's not lying!

31:03.988 --> 31:05.323
Who the fuck are you?

31:05.365 --> 31:06.449
I'm her fucking handler!

31:08.368 --> 31:09.285
I'm her handler.

31:10.411 --> 31:11.287
Listen...

31:11.996 --> 31:15.041
we popped her with a balloon
up her asshole at BDL

31:15.083 --> 31:17.960
and if she wants to keep her kid,
she works for us.

31:19.504 --> 31:21.297
Stop it, stop, don't touch me.

31:21.339 --> 31:23.299
Don't touch me. Don't touch...
Oh, wait.

31:23.341 --> 31:24.509
Shit, shit, shit.

31:24.550 --> 31:26.219
- Who's that?
- You wanna keep your door intact

31:26.260 --> 31:27.178
hit the mute button.

31:29.472 --> 31:32.225
Uh, yeah, that's a...
that's a No Go on Geronimo.

31:32.517 --> 31:34.936
I repeat, that's an NG on G-mo.

31:35.978 --> 31:37.480
OK, thank you.

31:37.522 --> 31:38.398
Fucking SWAT.

31:38.439 --> 31:40.650
A day without a battering ram
is like a day without sunshine.

31:40.691 --> 31:41.651
You're DEA?

31:42.193 --> 31:44.070
I think that's probably the worst question

31:44.112 --> 31:45.655
you could've asked me
at this moment in your life.

31:46.155 --> 31:47.407
Get up.

31:47.448 --> 31:48.699
- Is that all of it?
- Yes.

31:48.741 --> 31:50.034
- Get it.
- Excuse me...

31:50.076 --> 31:52.453
Take this directly to the Turk,
and if he doesn't blow your brains out

31:52.495 --> 31:54.497
because you're late or because,
I don't know, it's Tuesday

31:54.539 --> 31:57.417
and if we're able to take him down,
then maybe, maybe I'm not gonna

31:57.458 --> 32:00.128
stuff your ass down the hole in Niantic.

32:00.253 --> 32:02.046
- Go! Jesus Christ.
- You can't just walk out the--

32:02.088 --> 32:04.632
Hey, listen. Wait 48 hours,
you call this number.

32:04.841 --> 32:07.260
Whoever answers the phone, you tell 'em
Chino told you to call.

32:07.301 --> 32:10.388
You give him your details and Uncle Sam
will send you $10,000

32:10.430 --> 32:11.931
to get the front door fixed, OK?

32:12.432 --> 32:13.808
The front door's fine.

32:14.809 --> 32:16.018
They don't have to know that.

32:22.775 --> 32:23.693
You slapped me.

32:23.776 --> 32:25.820
Yeah, well, they needed
a little bit of a jolt.

32:26.028 --> 32:28.197
You rolled with it pretty good.

32:28.865 --> 32:30.116
Is that the money for Dockery?

32:30.324 --> 32:31.200
Uh...

32:31.659 --> 32:33.411
Is it OK if I don't explain it right now?

32:33.453 --> 32:35.913
As long as you don't tell the rest
of the family that I'm still in Bridgeport.

32:36.539 --> 32:37.915
Why are you still in Bridgeport?

32:40.084 --> 32:42.753
Hey, you know that gun
you keep at the office?

32:45.131 --> 32:46.007
Carry it.

32:46.549 --> 32:49.177
- You think that they'll--
- I doubt it, but you never know.

33:01.647 --> 33:02.982
Sure you don't want one of these?

33:03.274 --> 33:04.150
No.

33:13.242 --> 33:14.202
What're you doing?

33:15.369 --> 33:17.163
Mr Orr's local news homework.

33:18.623 --> 33:21.792
Oh, homework is this thing
when you do schoolwork

33:21.834 --> 33:24.337
when you get home from school...?

33:24.378 --> 33:25.671
- Never heard of it.
- Yeah.

33:25.713 --> 33:26.589
Yeah.

33:37.767 --> 33:38.976
Hey, put that out.

33:39.018 --> 33:41.270
- I'm blowing it out the window.
- No, right now.

33:43.481 --> 33:44.357
OK?

33:50.613 --> 33:52.365
- Now drink it.
- Bite me.

34:00.706 --> 34:01.624
What's going on with you?

34:03.125 --> 34:05.253
You don't want any of the clothes
I lifted at the mall.

34:05.586 --> 34:08.089
- You're this rabid anti-drug narc.
- Yep, that's me.

34:08.881 --> 34:10.508
Is it because of all the family shit?

34:10.883 --> 34:12.843
The mysterious return
of your long-lost cousin?

34:13.261 --> 34:15.054
The thing with that fucked-up cop?

34:17.890 --> 34:18.891
I don't know, I just...

34:21.060 --> 34:21.936
I don't know.

34:21.978 --> 34:22.853
OK...

34:25.648 --> 34:27.858
- Holy shit balls.
- What?

34:29.986 --> 34:30.861
That's him.

34:31.821 --> 34:34.115
That's the fucked-up cop
that I pointed the shotgun at.

34:35.408 --> 34:36.284
He's dead.

34:36.617 --> 34:37.952
Yeah, I, I see that.

34:37.994 --> 34:38.995
Who killed him?

34:43.416 --> 34:44.792
You talked to Sam?

34:45.459 --> 34:47.712
He knows me better than anybody
other than you.

34:48.379 --> 34:49.422
He hit on me.

34:50.756 --> 34:51.924
We have that in common.

34:53.342 --> 34:54.385
He didn't get anywhere.

34:54.969 --> 34:56.387
We have that in common too.

34:57.471 --> 34:58.848
How'd it go with Father Lebec?

35:01.309 --> 35:02.935
I know you better than anybody.

35:09.025 --> 35:10.234
Well, it went just fine.

35:10.610 --> 35:11.694
Told him everything.

35:12.987 --> 35:16.324
He gave me three Hail Marys
and asked me to kill the Monsignor for him.

35:21.454 --> 35:22.496
I chickened out.

35:25.041 --> 35:26.459
Didn't tell him a damn thing.

35:29.253 --> 35:31.505
I know it was an accident and all, but...

35:34.175 --> 35:35.843
I shot a man in the head.

35:37.637 --> 35:38.512
Killed him.

35:46.395 --> 35:47.271
Hey, you busy?

35:47.605 --> 35:48.481
Frantically.

35:48.773 --> 35:50.816
Make sure we keep a space open in the lot.

35:51.192 --> 35:52.109
We getting a VIP?

35:52.151 --> 35:55.821
No, it's the death car of that NYP
detective who got popped in Brett Woods.

35:55.863 --> 35:57.031
Fairfield's sending it over.

36:14.507 --> 36:15.633
Bernhardt Bail Bonds.

36:15.758 --> 36:16.634
<i>It's Moe.</i>

36:17.968 --> 36:18.886
Oh, hey.

36:19.303 --> 36:20.680
You seen that Caddy
parked around the corner?

36:20.721 --> 36:21.597
<i>Huh?</i>

36:21.889 --> 36:23.391
<i>It belongs to the housepainter.</i>

36:23.766 --> 36:25.601
<i>It's been sitting there a couple of days.</i>

36:26.936 --> 36:28.437
What the fuck happened, Otto?

36:29.689 --> 36:31.857
- You really want to know?
<i>- No, I don't.</i>

36:32.066 --> 36:34.235
I just don't need this blowing back on me.

36:34.402 --> 36:35.528
My brother and all that?

36:36.237 --> 36:39.323
Just move the fucking car. OK?

36:39.365 --> 36:40.324
<i>You owe me.</i>

36:45.663 --> 36:46.539
Who was that?

36:48.416 --> 36:49.375
Oh, it's just, um

36:50.459 --> 36:51.335
just Moe.

36:52.628 --> 36:55.548
It's end of the month,
he wants me to settle my tab.

37:17.027 --> 37:18.195
<i>He was a dirty cop.</i>

37:18.654 --> 37:20.489
<i>Had a falling out with the guys paying him.</i>

37:21.198 --> 37:23.909
<i>They drove him off the road,
put two in his chest, one in his head.</i>

37:24.285 --> 37:25.327
<i>Like the pros do.</i>

37:25.745 --> 37:26.704
Hey, Bright Eyes.

37:27.371 --> 37:28.873
Nice to know you respond to Bright Eyes.

37:29.206 --> 37:31.292
Only called your name three times.
Where'd you go?

37:32.460 --> 37:35.087
I was just thinking about
when he came in, the cop.

37:35.463 --> 37:36.422
What was his name?

37:36.756 --> 37:37.631
Oh, Winslow?

37:38.674 --> 37:41.635
I can't tell you how many people come through
that door I would never remember but...

37:42.303 --> 37:43.179
I remember him.

37:44.180 --> 37:45.097
The eye, maybe?

37:46.891 --> 37:48.768
Why'd Fairfield send it over?
They gonna do more tests?

37:49.185 --> 37:51.645
Nah, they're getting ready to wrap it up.
No witnesses.

37:52.480 --> 37:54.899
Vic had a long list of dubious asterisks
next to his name.

37:55.524 --> 37:57.818
Looks like the usual
dirtbag-on-dirtbag crime.

37:59.403 --> 38:01.238
I know we're supposed to give a shit,
brother in blue and all

38:01.280 --> 38:03.240
but I don't think there's a lot of tears
being shed.

38:05.659 --> 38:06.702
Then why is it here?

38:07.870 --> 38:10.539
Some lady detective from the NYPD
is coming up

38:10.831 --> 38:13.542
unofficially, of course, to make sure
us Connecticut yokels

38:13.584 --> 38:15.252
aren't as stupid as everyone thinks we are.

38:16.045 --> 38:17.171
They say she's the best.

38:17.463 --> 38:18.964
Highest closure rate in the city.

38:19.632 --> 38:22.551
I'm sure she's gonna wanna talk to you too,
since you're the only one that saw the guy

38:22.593 --> 38:24.303
so be sure to comb your hair, huh?

38:35.731 --> 38:37.483
- Hey, it's me.
<i>- You're late.</i>

38:37.858 --> 38:39.568
Yeah, something came up with my cousin.

38:40.611 --> 38:41.487
Where are you?

38:41.737 --> 38:42.696
<i>In the room.</i>

39:03.467 --> 39:04.802
Son of a bitch.

39:05.761 --> 39:07.179
Son of a bitch what?

39:08.222 --> 39:09.098
Uh...

39:09.974 --> 39:12.977
I came to get something out of the truck
and forgot my keys.

39:13.811 --> 39:14.687
They're in your hand.

39:16.897 --> 39:18.816
Well. That just makes it worse.

39:19.733 --> 39:22.486
I'm just happy to know I'm not the only one
losing their mind.

39:23.487 --> 39:25.698
Well, thank you, sweetheart.
That's very kind.

39:26.574 --> 39:27.491
What're you doing?

39:28.576 --> 39:29.702
I gotta go see Moe.

39:41.505 --> 39:42.464
Taylor, call me.

39:42.631 --> 39:43.716
We may have a problem.

40:19.376 --> 40:21.712
Pete, hi, how ya doin', buddy?
Thanks for calling.

40:21.754 --> 40:24.548
- Hey, Marius. How you doing, man?
<i>- Yeah, good.</i>

40:24.590 --> 40:27.134
I was a little surprised
when Tenzin said you wanted to talk.

40:27.176 --> 40:28.302
It must be important. What's going on?

40:28.344 --> 40:30.512
All that time that we were in together

40:30.554 --> 40:33.641
you, you know, you'd talk about
your grandparents and your cousin

40:33.682 --> 40:35.643
<i>- and the farm and all that.</i>
- Yeah.

40:35.684 --> 40:37.853
<i>But you never once, uh,
mentioned your mother.</i>

40:39.521 --> 40:42.149
- Yeah, so?
<i>- Well, this is the weird part.</i>

40:42.191 --> 40:45.819
I got a call yesterday from a woman
who says that she was your mother

40:45.861 --> 40:49.073
<i>and she was checking in
to see how you were doing.</i>

40:49.114 --> 40:50.282
That wasn't my mother.

40:51.116 --> 40:53.786
<i>- Are you sure? Because--</i>
- Yeah, I'm sure I'm sure.

40:54.536 --> 40:55.537
My mother's dead.

40:55.829 --> 40:56.705
She's dead?

40:57.665 --> 40:58.540
When did that happen?

41:00.000 --> 41:00.876
What do you care?

41:01.126 --> 41:03.087
- Well, we're friends, man.
<i>- Three years ago.</i>

41:03.754 --> 41:05.714
<i>She died three years ago.</i>

41:10.970 --> 41:11.845
Fuck.

41:13.722 --> 41:15.182
Alright, alright, alright...

41:33.951 --> 41:34.952
Hey, how you doing?

41:38.080 --> 41:39.123
Come on in, Pete.

41:40.541 --> 41:41.417
You go ahead.

41:42.876 --> 41:43.752
Come on.

41:49.967 --> 41:50.843
On the bed.

41:51.969 --> 41:52.928
You're right here.

41:57.182 --> 41:58.058
You know, Pete

41:58.350 --> 42:01.103
I thought you had a clear understanding
of what we expected from you

42:01.812 --> 42:06.150
and you waste a day looking into us?
What do you wanna know?

42:08.235 --> 42:11.030
We solve crimes for people
who can't go to the police.

42:12.406 --> 42:15.409
Guy who hired us tried others before,
ex-Blackwater guys

42:15.868 --> 42:18.203
but they didn't know shit
about cracking a mystery.

42:18.245 --> 42:20.914
They never found out about you
or your mother.

42:21.165 --> 42:22.249
I almost had her.

42:24.501 --> 42:26.003
Six months ago in Sedona.

42:27.463 --> 42:28.922
Saw her cross a busy street.

42:29.631 --> 42:33.469
Don't know how I spooked her,
but spook her I did.

42:33.844 --> 42:34.720
Here.

42:35.554 --> 42:36.430
Take a look at that.

42:37.097 --> 42:39.433
It might answer any questions
you still have about us.

42:41.351 --> 42:42.603
Show Pete where you are.

42:45.481 --> 42:46.648
<i>Showtime.</i>

42:49.818 --> 42:50.778
Ring a bell?

42:52.112 --> 42:52.988
Get in closer.

43:09.797 --> 43:12.508
We told you what would happen
if you fucked around.

43:21.475 --> 43:22.351
<i>Just a sec.</i>

43:25.479 --> 43:26.355
Don't.

43:27.481 --> 43:28.357
Please.

43:28.899 --> 43:31.276
I know who you are.
You don't have to do this.

43:34.738 --> 43:35.614
<i>You don't.</i>

43:35.906 --> 43:37.825
<i>Oh, but I think we do, Pete.</i>

43:38.575 --> 43:39.952
Please don't do this.

43:44.456 --> 43:45.374
Jesus.

43:49.169 --> 43:50.045
Pete?

43:50.337 --> 43:52.422
- Get your gun and shoot through the door.
<i>- What?</i>

43:52.464 --> 43:53.340
Do it! Do it!

43:54.842 --> 43:56.301
<i>Goddammit...</i>

44:06.436 --> 44:07.855
<i>He warned her. She's got a Colt</i>

44:07.896 --> 44:08.981
pointed at your heart.

44:11.316 --> 44:12.234
Can I help you?

44:12.985 --> 44:14.570
Sorry. Wrong house.

44:19.074 --> 44:23.036
What're you doing? We're just gonna go back
after dark, plug her through the window

44:23.078 --> 44:24.079
when her kids are home.

44:26.707 --> 44:27.875
Then shoot me now.

44:28.750 --> 44:29.835
Cos if you don't...

44:30.169 --> 44:33.463
and you hurt her or anyone in that family,
I will get a gun

44:33.505 --> 44:34.798
and I will fucking eat it

44:34.840 --> 44:37.050
and you will never find my mother
or the money.

44:39.428 --> 44:40.929
Now you know who I am.

44:46.059 --> 44:46.935
Wow.

45:01.116 --> 45:02.117
Spread that out.

45:02.951 --> 45:03.827
Wh... why?

45:05.579 --> 45:06.622
Spread that out.

45:15.380 --> 45:16.506
What're you doing, man?

45:19.968 --> 45:21.303
You, you

45:21.845 --> 45:22.804
stand on it.

45:23.096 --> 45:24.097
No, man.

45:25.682 --> 45:26.767
Stand on it.

45:27.392 --> 45:30.562
What're you doing, man? This is bullshit.

45:32.689 --> 45:33.815
You don't need to do this.

45:36.151 --> 45:37.027
Look at him.

45:39.529 --> 45:40.405
Listen...

45:44.284 --> 45:45.160
Choose.

45:45.702 --> 45:46.578
Choose?

45:47.079 --> 45:48.288
What the fuck does that mean?

45:49.206 --> 45:50.082
"Choose"?

45:50.165 --> 45:52.709
Choose. Or I will do them both.

45:54.544 --> 45:55.504
- Me.
- Just shut up!

45:55.545 --> 45:56.421
You shut up!

45:56.713 --> 45:58.131
- A hero?
- Listen...

45:58.548 --> 45:59.925
Fuckin' love it when I get a hero.

46:00.801 --> 46:02.970
But sometimes, just to prove a point

46:04.263 --> 46:05.389
you have to do the other one.

46:06.139 --> 46:07.933
- Stop, stop--
- No, no, no...

46:11.520 --> 46:12.396
Or not.

46:18.860 --> 46:19.820
Stop, stop...

46:22.906 --> 46:24.116
Take it out, take it out...

46:32.541 --> 46:33.750
Now you know who we are.

46:35.919 --> 46:37.087
Roll him up, sweetheart.

46:39.006 --> 46:39.881
This is on you.

47:02.612 --> 47:06.241
You get squirrely, an anonymous call
goes to a local tip-line

47:07.159 --> 47:10.954
brings your friend here to light,
with your prints and your DNA.

47:11.872 --> 47:13.123
Take the fucking knife.

47:17.169 --> 47:18.045
The rags.

47:22.591 --> 47:23.467
Fill it in.

47:33.685 --> 47:39.858
<i>♪ Don't want no streetcar love
Oh, oh no ♪</i>

47:41.443 --> 47:47.949
<i>♪ One who'll carry out a one-hour ride
Oh no, oh no ♪</i>

47:49.534 --> 47:52.829
<i>♪ I just want a little girl to... ♪</i>

48:00.212 --> 48:03.006
We've gotten further than the muscle-heads
did before us

48:03.090 --> 48:06.426
which gives us some leeway,
but not an infinite amount.

48:06.676 --> 48:09.805
We don't have to kill anybody to give 'em
the worst fucking day of their lives.

48:10.430 --> 48:12.349
Remember that when you look at your family.

48:13.475 --> 48:16.520
By my watch, you have 48 hours
to locate your mother.

48:18.188 --> 48:19.064
Get out.

48:34.996 --> 48:35.872
Gina...

48:38.417 --> 48:39.292
I'm so...

49:25.505 --> 49:27.757
- What the actual fuck?
<i>- Look, I'm sorry about that--</i>

49:27.799 --> 49:31.386
You're sorry? I almost shot someone
through my door.

49:31.428 --> 49:32.888
<i>Yeah, I was, uh...</i>

49:32.929 --> 49:34.848
I was actually watching your house.

49:34.890 --> 49:35.765
What?

49:36.391 --> 49:40.353
<i>In case that Desmond guy came back.
I, I, uh, I didn't wanna tell you</i>

49:40.395 --> 49:43.231
<i>because I... I thought I was being paranoid</i>

49:43.273 --> 49:44.566
<i>and then I saw somebody walk up</i>

49:44.608 --> 49:46.485
and I got freaked out, uh...

49:47.736 --> 49:49.362
- so then I followed him.
<i>- Who was he?</i>

49:49.404 --> 49:50.947
This guy I almost shot?

49:50.989 --> 49:53.200
<i>He was just some guy
who was selling magazines.</i>

49:53.241 --> 49:54.117
Oh, for f...

49:54.993 --> 49:56.036
Why didn't you call me?

49:58.538 --> 50:01.500
- Uh, because my phone died.
<i>- Then you borrow a phone.</i>

50:01.541 --> 50:04.753
<i>You steal a phone!
I was freaking the fuck out.</i>

50:04.794 --> 50:09.216
<i>I had the kids go to Gloria's.
I didn't know if something happened to you.</i>

50:11.218 --> 50:14.596
Well, I'm fine, you're fine.
I overreacted. I gotta go.

50:14.638 --> 50:15.514
<i>OK?</i>

50:16.973 --> 50:17.849
Pete.

50:18.099 --> 50:18.975
<i>What?</i>

50:21.353 --> 50:22.729
Thanks for looking out for me

50:23.772 --> 50:27.317
but never do anything like that again.

50:30.153 --> 50:31.029
OK.

50:35.659 --> 50:39.788
Marius... that's seriously fucked up.

50:42.749 --> 50:43.625
I know.

50:48.088 --> 50:50.340
You said you'd kill yourself
if they harmed Julia?

50:50.382 --> 50:51.633
I had to say something.

50:55.595 --> 50:56.638
I spoke to Pete.

50:58.640 --> 51:00.016
He said his mother's dead.

51:00.517 --> 51:01.434
That is not good.

51:01.810 --> 51:03.895
No, it is. He's lying.

51:05.105 --> 51:06.731
He said she died three years ago

51:06.773 --> 51:11.069
but the two assholes said that they saw her
in Sedona six months ago.

51:11.319 --> 51:13.280
But Pete could really think she's dead, so.

51:13.780 --> 51:15.657
Either way, I gotta work him to find her.

51:15.699 --> 51:17.409
On the phone? You already tried that.

51:17.450 --> 51:18.827
- I know.
- You can't go and see him

51:18.868 --> 51:20.579
- you switched your records.
- I know that too.

51:20.620 --> 51:22.998
Well, how do you plan on working him?

51:23.164 --> 51:24.165
Face-to-face.

51:25.542 --> 51:26.710
You wanna get him out?

51:27.002 --> 51:28.253
Well, I don't <i>want</i> to.

51:28.295 --> 51:32.799
Even if it was possible, it would pose
an existential threat to you, Marius.

51:32.841 --> 51:35.218
If real Pete has any contact
with his family, you're burned.

51:35.260 --> 51:37.721
At best, you'll get popped
for identity theft.

51:37.846 --> 51:38.930
You'll go back to prison.

51:38.972 --> 51:42.350
At worst, you get stabbed in the heart
and rolled up in a shower curtain.

51:47.230 --> 51:49.357
I don't see that we have any other choice.

51:51.026 --> 51:53.320
When did this become "we"?
I thought I was doing some research.

51:53.361 --> 51:55.572
Straight split, minus expenses.

51:55.614 --> 51:57.407
That could be $5 million.

51:57.449 --> 51:59.743
That's retire-on-a-beach-in-Bali money.

51:59.868 --> 52:02.871
- I don't like Bali.
- So then retire to the Geordie shore.

52:08.126 --> 52:09.836
Getting Pete out of
prison would take weeks.

52:10.670 --> 52:11.671
Do we have weeks?

52:12.380 --> 52:14.007
No, we have tomorrow.

52:16.635 --> 52:17.510
Tomorrow.

52:18.845 --> 52:19.721
Yeah.

52:22.849 --> 52:24.726
How do you feel about going to prison?
